sub_title: MSc CISSP - Junior Researcher Risk Management & Cybersecurity
summary:
As an Information Security consultant I first and foremost strive for customer focus and attention to detail to protect and enhance business value of customer organizations.

With focus on security that covers people, processes and technology, my solid understanding of both technical and governance disciplines of security helps me to support the business in finding solutions to complex IT and security challenges.

People that have closely worked with me have described me as a person that is driven and consistently brings value and positive results to the organization through my attention to detail, big-picture insight, and deep understanding of organizational intricacies. My focus on integrity and duty help me form an integral and invaluable asset from both information security and overall organizational and business perspectives.

projects:
[{'title': 'Dajmo, Zeleni, Zeleni!', 'date': {'start': {'month': 2, 'day': None, 'year': 2014}, 'end': {'month': 6, 'day': None, 'year': 2014}}, 'description': 'The project “Dajmo, zeleni, zeleni!” was a part of a bigger framework of the project “Interactive Learning is Fun” (inLIF) Netherlands. It was carried out in cooperation with foreign and local partners with the target population being children, parents, teachers and caretakers in kindergartens, schools and other institutions in Slovenia. 

The purpose of the program was to bring together children and their parents in creative playing and activities through a series of exercises and specific techniques written and sent to the participating mentors. The creative work was centered on the main story called “Dajmo, zeleni, zeleni!” which was dedicated to the Slovenian athletes at the Winter Olympic Games Sochi 2014.

National athletes often work as role models in society and especially in Slovenia they often bring the people together, rejuvenate their spirits and inspire solidarity. As such, they were a source of great inspiration. inLIF techniques inspire creative flexibility and self-discovery. 
Letting creativity flow naturally and with improved interaction, brought the program to life and helped bring the activities they experienced into their everyday lives as a style of healthier living in which interaction plays a larger role than before. Empathetically experiencing the Olympic Games also encourages parents and children towards greater optimism and achievement, which is another important aim for us.

The program attracted the participation of 69 different institutions, 189 mentors and approximately 2,500 children. 

The main partners in the program were:
- Ice Hockey Federation of Slovenia, 
- Ministry of Education, Science and Sport of the Republic of Slovenia, 
- All of Europe Reads to Kids - pan-European reading promotion initiative
